commit message:
- Improved blacklist support
- Added some typical mobile mac addresses to bssid blacklist
- Added basic UI elements for blacklist on Overview screen
Test run
Test run 2
Added build.txt
Unknown wifis (= not yet in wifi catalog) are marked in database
Simple cluster mechanism for Wifi Catalog Objects
Location based blacklist (don't log within certain area)
Less restrictive bssid filters (too many false positives)
Experimental: Android 2.2 support
missing super.onDestroy
Cleaning up
Experimental: display all sessions' data (http://code.google.com/p/openbmap/issues/detail?id=36), UI control elements yet missing
Cleanup: Removed files not needed anymore
Bugfix: mark new wifis fixed
More filter options for wifi overview (context menu)
Moved filter menu to list header
Added layer selector mapview

Breaking change: no more colons in mac address (wifi export), cell export now includes rxlevel for serving cell

Bumped version to 0.7.6
Added option to re-organize database (aka sqlite vacuum)

Fixed rotation issue (http://code.google.com/p/openbmap/issues/detail?id=41)
Increased upload grace time for slow uploads (http://code.google.com/p/openbmap/issues/detail?id=43)
Accelerated GPX export by exporting only strongest wifi measurement (instead of all for given bssid)
Re-introduced fail-safe zoom to improve first time user experience (otherwise map is on zoom level 1 on first start)
Fixed a bug where progress dialog was appearing although no export taking place
Improved UMTS and HSDPA handling (http://code.google.com/p/openbmap/issues/detail?id=39)
Minor UI glitches (Defect Network type, Missing Is new wifi indicator)
Export file time stamp changed to creation date instead of export date (http://code.google.com/p/openbmap/issues/detail?id=45)
Bug in filename generation fixed (relates to http://code.google.com/p/openbmap/issues/detail?id=45)

Added settings entry for home-zone blacklist (don't scan around your home)
Added settings entry to anonymise SSIDS
added disclaimer on upgrade data loss
Overwrite existing wifi catalog on update
Overwrite old maps on update
